# Copy to .env or set in your host (e.g. Render → Environment). Never commit real passwords.
# If DATABASE_URL is rejected, ensure the host is the full hostname (with domain), include :5432 if required,
# and add ?sslmode=require for cloud Postgres. Special characters in the password must be URL-encoded.
#
# Render: If you see "could not translate host name dpg-xxxxx-a", the internal hostname is not resolving.
# Fix: In Render Dashboard → your Postgres → copy the **External Database URL** (host ends in
# .REGION-postgres.render.com), set it as DATABASE_URL on the web service, and ensure ?sslmode=require
# (the app adds sslmode=require automatically for *.postgres.render.com). Alternatively link the DB to
# the web service in the same region so the internal connectionString works.

# SQLite (default):
# DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./fruit_vegetable_costs.db

# Supabase: use the Postgres connection string only (Database → Connection string → URI).
# Transaction pooler (port 6543) is recommended for APIs. Append ?sslmode=require if needed.
# After switching, restart the server and re-upload sales + P&L (empty Supabase DB has no rows).
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://postgres.[ref]:PASSWORD@aws-0-REGION.pooler.supabase.com:6543/postgres?sslmode=require

# Branding (optional). Do not set ERP_COMPANY_TAGLINE to the same text as ERP_COMPANY_NAME.
# ERP_COMPANY_NAME=Your Company Name
# ERP_COMPANY_TAGLINE=
# ERP_LOGO_URL=https://xxx.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/bucket/logo.png
